# Choosable premount ignore list — ISO9660 root directory entries
# that must NOT be overwritten for premount cpio injection.
#
# One pattern per line.  Empty lines and #-comments are ignored.
# Trailing * means prefix match (e.g. MD5SUM* matches MD5SUM, MD5SUM.TXT, MD5SUMS).
# Otherwise the entire name is matched exactly.
# All matching is case-insensitive.
#
# Why these are excluded:
#   MD5SUM*       — GRUB uses if [ -f /MD5SUM.TXT ] for integrity checks
#   README*       — boot scripts / GRUB may reference README.DISKDEFINES etc.
#   UBUNTU*       — referenced by Ubuntu GRUB as /UBUNTU sentinel file
#   DEBIAN*       — referenced by Debian GRUB as /DEBIAN sentinel file
#   POP*          — referenced by Pop!_OS GRUB as /POP sentinel file
#   AUTORUN.INF   — Windows autorun, occasionally checked
#   .ALPINE_RELEASE — Alpine Linux requires this file to detect the live medium

MD5SUM*
README*
UBUNTU*
DEBIAN*
POP*
AUTORUN.INF
EFI.IMG
SHA256SUM.TXT
.ALPINE_RELEASE
